<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">How many gallons of white house paint are so=
ld in the US every year?</h2>



<p>Find the number of homes in the US: Assuming that there are 300 million =
people in the US and the average household contains 2.5 people then we can =
conclude that there are 120 million homes in the US.</p>



<p>Number of houses: Many people live in apartments and other types of buil=
dings different than houses. Let=E2=80=99s assume that the percentage of pe=
ople living in houses is 50%. Hence, there are 60 million houses.</p>



<p>Houses that are painted in white: Although white is the most popular col=
or, many people choose different paint colors for their houses or do not ne=
ed to paint them (using other types of techniques in order to cover the ext=
ernal surface of the house). Let=E2=80=99s hypothesize that 30% of all hous=
es are painted in white, which makes 18 million houses that are painted in =
white.</p>



<p>Repainting: People need to repaint their houses after a given amount of =
years. For the purposes of this exercise, let=E2=80=99s hypothesize that pe=
ople repaint their houses once every 9 years, which means that every years =
2 million houses are repainted in white.</p>



<p>I have never painted a house, but let=E2=80=99s assume that in order to =
repaint a house you need 30 gallons of white paint. This means the total US=
 market for white house paint is 60 million gallons.</p>



